"{\"uid\": \"thenorthlines.com-paris-transforms-as-2024-olympics-opening-extravaganza-arrives-amidst-citywide-fervor\", \"text\": \"\\\"Paris turn Olympic extravaganza as Games spirit sweeps the city\\\"  As the highly anticipated Olympics 2024 opening ceremony approaches, the iconic city of Paris is immersed in a celebratory mood despite some hiccups along the way. With just days to go for the commencement of the biggest sporting spectacle, strict security measures are causing disruptions for locals even as the city transforms into a one giant stadium.  From the banks of the scenic River Seine to the world-famous landmarks like Eiffel Tower and Notre Dame, the Olympic five rings and colors can be seen draped across every nook and corner filling residents and visitors with a sense of excitement. In an unprecedented initiative, the opening ceremony will feature a lavish floating spectacle on the Seine witnessed by thousands lining up its shores.  While preparations for such a grand global event are bound to cause inconveniences, many Parisians have voiced concerns over restricted movement, business losses and large-scale annoyances. Transport rates hike and intermittent metro closures have added to citizens' woes. However, with the action set to begin, hopes are high that the Olympic fever will overshadow all problems. After Tokyo hosted limited capacity events, Paris promises a grand showcase.  From over 10,000 competitors across 200-plus nations to 329 medal events in 32 sports, the scale is sure to be spectacular. Unconventional creative decisions also underscore the French spirit of doing things distinctively. With athletes now able to perform in front iconic backdrops, Paris looks primed to stage a momentous return of the Summer Games to its fascinating venue and vibe. As the inaugural event looms large, the sweeping stadium that is Paris awaits a celebration for the ages.  thenorthlines.com is a leading digital platform covering and disseminating the news, views and allied information on evolving public policies and responses pertaining to Indian subcontinent and its neighbourhood with a particular focus on the north India region.  \\u00a9 2024 Northlines. All Rights Reserved. Powered byRodiex Services LLP\"}"